{
  "texts": [
    "He did not have any concrete ideas regarding composition, palette, style, etc., and he would not have been able to create any of these images without GenAI.Contrast this with Jill, an experienced visual artist working on campaign visuals for an environmental protection agency.",
    "She wants to create an image of a polluted ocean in the palm of a hand to correspond with key mission statements.",
    "Starting from a hand-drawn sketch, Jill refines her prompts, guiding the GenAI through a series of many images and exerting precise control, e.g., by using inpainting and ControlNet [87] to pose the hand and steer the composition, until she gets an image that conforms to her concrete expectations.",
    "Jill already knew what image she wanted and could have created something similar by different means, say with Photoshop.",
    "Here, CCC can ground why Jill deserves a significant credit share and that GenAI is more akin to a tool than a full-fledged creator.CCC can capture the difference between these cases in a systematic fashion."
  ]
}